Description: Software Token for cryptographic authentication stoken is a software token which generates one-time passwords compatible with RSA SecurID 128-bit (AES) tokens.  SecurID tokens are commonly used to authenticate end users to protected network resources and VPNs, as OTPs provide greater resistance to many attacks associated with static passwords. . stoken aims to provide a Linux-friendly, free software alternative to the proprietary RSA SecurID Software Authenticators.
Package-List: libstoken-dev deb libdevel optional arch=any libstoken1t64 deb libs optional arch=any stoken deb utils optional arch=any
